<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-30-0427 </DOCNO><TEXT>In order to help the greenhouse industry with the burden of energy costs,the Canadian government has provided funds for research and demonstrationsinto solutions to reduce the impact that energy costs have on the greenhouseindustry. This report provides information on the known recent or ongoinggreenhouse energy research, development and demonstration projects inCanada. The greenhouse program encompasses the reduction of heating costsby developing and evaluating waste heat utilization systems and sources,economic solar heating systems, retractable insulation systems, ventilationheat exchangers, optimal temperature regimes that reduce energy consumptionwithout adversely affecting crop productivity, microprocessors for preciseenvironmental control and optimized energy usage. 4 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>